<item>
            <title>[SOLR-953] Small simplification for LuceneGapFragmenter.isNewFragment</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-953</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This little patch makes the code for LuceneGapFragmenter.isNewFragment(Token) slightly more intuitive.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The method currently features the line&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;fragOffsetAccum += token.endOffset() - fragOffsetAccum;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This can be simplified, though, to just&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;fragOffsetAccum = token.endOffset();
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Maybe it&apos;s just me, but I find the latter expression&apos;s intent to be sufficiently clearer than the former to warrant committing such a change.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This patch makes this simplification. Also, if you do make this simplification, then it doesn&apos;t really make sense to think of fragOffsetAccum as an accumulator anymore, so in the patch we rename the variable to just fragOffset.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Tests from HighlighterTest.java pass with the patch applied.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
